WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.300
<i> Lidia: Previously</i>
<i> on "moonshine".</i>

00:02.436 --> 00:04.670
Ryan: So, you're sammy's mom,
and I'm sammy's father?

00:04.672 --> 00:06.638
Rhian: Get ready for
your minds to be blown.

00:06.640 --> 00:09.207
I am having twins! Woo!

00:09.209 --> 00:11.410
- Ryan says you're
a professor in new york.

00:11.479 --> 00:13.278
- Archaeology.
- Oh cool!

00:13.314 --> 00:15.146
- Think you should
take some time.

00:15.182 --> 00:17.182
- Are you breaking up with me?

00:17.318 --> 00:20.118
- Gale killed milk crate mike.
My druggie ex?

00:20.187 --> 00:22.687
- Boss, we gotta talk.
- Gale's a murderer.

00:22.823 --> 00:24.522
Terry: We can finally have
our own place.

00:24.558 --> 00:27.259
- Terry, I am leaving foxton.

00:27.394 --> 00:29.160
Lidia: Hey, hun.
I was worried.

00:29.196 --> 00:30.796
- Yeah, you should be.

00:30.865 --> 00:32.531
I was just showing the boys
here their new home.

00:32.533 --> 00:33.898
(engine revs)

00:35.403 --> 00:37.136
("sunny days" by lighthouse)

00:37.271 --> 00:39.337
(keys clack)

00:43.010 --> 00:45.544
<i> Lidia: Summer vacation's</i>
<i> a big deal at the moonshine.</i>

00:45.546 --> 00:47.612
<i> People wait all year</i>

00:47.681 --> 00:49.514
<i> For their two weeks</i>
<i> of maximum chill.</i>

00:50.584 --> 00:52.750
<i> As such, it's important</i>
<i> to cram in</i>

00:52.787 --> 00:54.419
<i> As much fun as you can,</i>

00:54.422 --> 00:56.588
<i>Before returning to the numbing</i>
<i> oblivion</i>

00:56.590 --> 00:59.224
<i> That is 97% of your life.</i>

00:59.260 --> 01:00.892
(hair ruffles)

01:00.928 --> 01:04.028
<i> People come for the view,</i>
<i> the warm, salty air,</i>

01:04.065 --> 01:05.964
<i> The glorious beach.</i>

01:05.966 --> 01:07.232
(bottles clang)

01:07.234 --> 01:09.001
<i> Then stay, because they're</i>
<i> paralyzed</i>

01:09.136 --> 01:11.069
<i> By my father's famous</i>
<i> moonshine.</i>

01:11.105 --> 01:12.904
<i> Home-stilled.</i>

01:12.940 --> 01:14.406
<i> 140 proof rum.</i>

01:14.408 --> 01:16.241
♪ lyin' in the sun
with your radio ♪

01:16.243 --> 01:18.910
<i> No one misses or remembers,</i>

01:18.946 --> 01:21.380
<i> Our annual labour day</i>
<i> moonshine party.</i>

01:21.515 --> 01:23.849
<i> The moonshine campground</i>
<i> and cottages</i>

01:23.918 --> 01:25.717
<i> Is the destination of choice</i>

01:25.753 --> 01:27.586
<i> For generations of campers.</i>

01:27.655 --> 01:30.522
<i> Which is why seasonals</i>
<i> like little oink,</i>

01:30.657 --> 01:32.390
<i> Get the red beach</i>
<i> towel treatment.</i>

01:32.426 --> 01:34.126
- What's up?

01:34.128 --> 01:36.795
<i> - His family's reserved the</i>
<i> same site for over 30 years.</i>

01:36.930 --> 01:38.997
<i> When you book your vacay</i>
<i> at the moonshine,</i>

01:39.066 --> 01:40.899
<i>It's always a memorable summer.</i>

01:42.837 --> 01:44.670
<i> Guaranteed.</i>

01:44.805 --> 01:46.604
(motorcycle engine rumbles)
woman: Look out, buddy!

01:46.640 --> 01:49.074
Biker: Outta the way!

01:49.076 --> 01:50.242
(engine rumbles)

01:50.377 --> 01:52.811
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh

01:52.813 --> 01:54.579
- Ugh.

01:55.649 --> 01:57.749
♪ this is my life,
this is my life ♪

