♪ this is my life,
my life ♪

02:07.461 --> 02:09.761
♪♪♪

02:09.830 --> 02:11.363
Rhian: Who knew crushing
tax debt

02:11.365 --> 02:14.633
Was such an aphrodisiac?
- Upside,

02:14.635 --> 02:16.901
Thanks to my botched
criminal career,

02:16.937 --> 02:19.605
The tax debt is now only $290k.

02:19.740 --> 02:21.239
- Oh, good.

02:21.308 --> 02:23.375
So much more doable
than the $350k.

02:23.377 --> 02:25.244
- Uh, hey.

02:25.379 --> 02:27.579
So, because of our
biker infestation,

02:27.615 --> 02:29.448
Little oink is thinking
of cutting his vacay short.

02:29.450 --> 02:31.750
Rhian: What?
- And if he bails,

02:31.819 --> 02:34.319
(engine revs)
- all the campers bail.

02:34.321 --> 02:36.854
(motorcycle rumbles past)

02:36.991 --> 02:38.724
How do you propose
we fix this?

02:38.726 --> 02:40.459
- How is this all on me, again?

02:40.461 --> 02:42.260
- 'cause you screwed the biker.

02:42.262 --> 02:44.129
Now the biker's screwing us.
- Argh! God!

02:44.198 --> 02:45.997
None of this would be happening
if my cheating,

02:46.033 --> 02:48.066
Self-absorbed ex hadn't gone
all emo confessional

02:48.068 --> 02:49.834
With said biker
in the men's washroom.

02:49.904 --> 02:53.004
- Well, maybe I did reveal
more things than I should've.

02:53.073 --> 02:54.740
- Can't you just talk to gale?

02:54.875 --> 02:57.008
He was your boyfriend
until yesterday.

02:57.044 --> 02:58.577
- We didn't really do labels.

02:58.712 --> 03:01.380
Ugh, okay. Fine.

03:01.515 --> 03:03.081
I'll try.

03:03.217 --> 03:04.816
- 'cause it's the right
thing to do.

03:04.885 --> 03:06.685
The selfless thing to do.

03:07.755 --> 03:09.520
Which is important.

03:09.557 --> 03:11.890
- And the man-toddler
graduates to a man-child.

03:12.025 --> 03:13.692
- Huh.

03:13.761 --> 03:15.160
(engines rumbling)

03:15.229 --> 03:16.828
Woman: There he is, see?
Man: Ah!

03:16.964 --> 03:19.030
(indistinct chatter)

03:19.066 --> 03:20.766
(beer bottles clink)

03:22.903 --> 03:24.703
Lidia: Thank you for being open

03:24.772 --> 03:26.905
To having a dialogue with me.
- I'm not open to it.

03:27.040 --> 03:28.373
You came, you sat,

03:28.442 --> 03:30.842
You liberated my beer.

03:30.844 --> 03:32.844
- And you showed up
to my parents'

03:32.846 --> 03:34.580
Community theatre performance

03:34.715 --> 03:36.180
With the cast of "leather
daddies".

03:36.217 --> 03:38.150
Bit much, no?
- I had to send a message.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.419
(birds chirping)

03:42.456 --> 03:44.222
(bottle clinks)

03:44.258 --> 03:45.857
(sunglasses rattle)

03:45.859 --> 03:47.526
- Look, I...

03:47.661 --> 03:49.294
I know you're hurt.

03:49.429 --> 03:52.397
- You think I'm upset because
you wanted to dump me?

03:52.433 --> 03:55.366
You were planning a move
against the club, lidia.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.570
You used me.
- Oh, come on.

03:58.572 --> 04:01.806
"gale"? Like you weren't
using me too?

04:01.875 --> 04:03.408
As cute as I looked
in my heidi get up,

04:03.410 --> 04:05.143
And I looked frickin' adorable,

04:05.279 --> 04:06.678
You can't deny part
of the attraction

04:06.714 --> 04:08.846
Was what I could offer you.
- You're the one who said

04:08.882 --> 04:10.214
We shouldn't mix business
and pleasure,

04:10.251 --> 04:12.617
And you were right.
So, this, you and me,

04:12.620 --> 04:14.552
Now it's all business.

04:14.588 --> 04:16.220
The moonshine's mine.

04:16.257 --> 04:17.555
- What is this, "braveheart"?

04:17.591 --> 04:19.491
You can't just show up
and pillage!

04:19.626 --> 04:21.460
- It's a direct order
from the chapter president.

04:21.462 --> 04:23.495
We needed a legitimate business

04:23.564 --> 04:25.564
To run our organization
through. It's a perfect fit.

04:25.566 --> 04:27.499
I mean, hidden cove.

04:27.568 --> 04:29.767
Cash transactions.
High turnover.

04:30.971 --> 04:33.305
You said you'd do anything
to protect your family.

04:33.307 --> 04:35.707
Well, I gotta do what I gotta
do to protect mine.

04:35.743 --> 04:37.843
- My family consists of four
mentally unstable siblings,

04:37.845 --> 04:39.978
Two teenagers,
and a couple of seniors.

04:40.113 --> 04:42.146
You wanna fight?
This is not a fair match.

04:44.217 --> 04:46.718
- It's not a fight
when you've already lost.

04:46.787 --> 04:53.058
♪♪♪

04:53.193 --> 04:54.860
- God!

04:54.995 --> 04:56.795
(sand crunches underfoot)

04:56.864 --> 04:58.730
You know what?
I just have to know.

04:58.799 --> 05:00.932
Did you murder
"milk crate mike"?

05:01.001 --> 05:04.268
- Milk... I have no idea
who "milk crate mike" is.

05:04.305 --> 05:05.804
What is with your family?

05:05.873 --> 05:08.807
And the-the cutesy nicknames?
- Yay or nay on the murdering?

05:08.876 --> 05:12.077
- Okay, you wanna talk
about criminal behaviour?

05:12.146 --> 05:13.911
You framed jill leblanc

05:13.947 --> 05:16.214
With the help of a foxton
police officer.

05:16.216 --> 05:18.216
You laundered money,
you hijacked a truck.

05:18.351 --> 05:20.151
- You're linked to every
one of those crimes.

05:20.286 --> 05:22.220
- That's true,
but I had nothing to do

05:22.222 --> 05:25.223
With the dead body your folks
buried in the front yard.

05:25.225 --> 05:29.694
♪♪♪

05:29.697 --> 05:31.596
- Are you blackmailing me?

05:33.166 --> 05:34.465
- Not if you cooperate.

05:37.037 --> 05:38.536
Lidia...

05:40.307 --> 05:41.806
You and me,

05:43.844 --> 05:45.476
Was any of it real?

05:48.615 --> 05:50.649
- I was gonna ask you
the same thing.

05:50.784 --> 05:56.588
♪♪♪

05:58.859 --> 06:00.658
(motorcycle engines rumble)

06:00.694 --> 06:02.661
<i> (bikers shout indistinctly)</i>
<i> sammy: Hey!</i>

06:02.796 --> 06:04.463
You okay?

06:04.598 --> 06:07.532
- Is this a common occurrence?
Thugs hanging out on the lawn?

06:07.534 --> 06:11.169
- Uh... Recent campground
amenity.

06:12.539 --> 06:14.539
- Huh. You don't seem
very bothered by it.

06:14.575 --> 06:16.941
- Given everything that's been
going on around here lately,

06:17.010 --> 06:19.077
Couple bikers,

06:19.212 --> 06:20.812
Sorta pales in comparison.

06:20.947 --> 06:22.748
- (chuckles) to what?

06:24.317 --> 06:26.084
Sammy, I'm not trying
to be judgy.

06:26.086 --> 06:27.819
- Okay, good,
'cause after everything

06:27.954 --> 06:29.888
We talked about last night,

06:29.890 --> 06:31.823
You feeling judged
your whole life,

06:31.892 --> 06:34.726
It just sort of feels like
you're doing the same to us.

06:34.795 --> 06:36.428
Ryan: Awww!

06:36.430 --> 06:38.530
Look at you two!

06:38.599 --> 06:40.965
Making up for lost time.
It's beautiful!

06:41.034 --> 06:42.834
Come on, group hug!
- Ryan!

06:42.870 --> 06:44.569
- Bring in the love.

06:44.605 --> 06:51.843
♪♪♪

06:51.879 --> 06:53.511
(low hum of chatter)

06:55.582 --> 06:59.183
♪♪♪

06:59.219 --> 07:02.320
Crystal: And any foxton cove
business association member

07:02.456 --> 07:05.356
Who signs up for a weekly
cleaning subscription today

07:05.392 --> 07:08.293
Will not only receive
20 percent off,

07:08.295 --> 07:11.596
But also, a crystal clean
water bottle!

07:11.632 --> 07:13.598
While supplies last.

07:13.634 --> 07:15.733
I will now take questions.

07:15.769 --> 07:18.269
- Do you still live
on the moonshine grounds?

07:18.305 --> 07:20.405
- I currently live
at my mother's.

07:20.407 --> 07:22.707
- The one who's in jail?
- I only have one mother.

07:22.743 --> 07:25.210
- Are you still dating
that drunk hooligan?

07:25.279 --> 07:27.746
- No.
Um, I fired him,

07:27.881 --> 07:29.681
And he has chosen to be
with his long-lost love

07:29.683 --> 07:31.616
And they have a full-grown
son now, so.

07:31.618 --> 07:34.085
- Yo, someone tell me
why I'm here?

07:34.087 --> 07:35.820
I was told there would be
free pastries,

07:35.823 --> 07:37.989
And there are none left.
Woman: Yeah!

07:37.991 --> 07:40.859
- You were invited here today,
sir, because we,

07:40.861 --> 07:42.760
As proud pillars
of the community,

07:42.762 --> 07:45.096
Are concerned for the welfare
of moonshine campers.

07:45.231 --> 07:47.031
The finley-cullens
are criminals.

07:47.033 --> 07:48.767
- This is an ambush!
Katie: No.

07:48.902 --> 07:51.402
Your family is responsible
for ruining this town,

07:51.472 --> 07:53.237
And everybody needs to know it.

07:53.273 --> 07:55.640
- Are they responsible
for that haircut?

07:55.676 --> 07:57.943
- As a matter of fact, yes.
- (gasping)

07:58.078 --> 07:59.778
- If you value your life,

07:59.780 --> 08:01.780
And your precious
two weeks of vacation,

08:01.782 --> 08:04.382
You will help me to restore
dignity to foxton

08:04.384 --> 08:07.184
By signing this petition.
Group: Yes.

08:07.221 --> 08:09.354
- No! Oink! Don't listen!

08:09.489 --> 08:11.456
(chairs clattering,
group muttering)

08:11.458 --> 08:13.391
The moonshine...

08:13.393 --> 08:15.794
Is a force for good.

08:15.929 --> 08:18.396
The local economy
depends on us.

08:18.398 --> 08:21.032
Campers need to stop for gas,
groceries,

08:21.068 --> 08:23.534
Souvenirs from mcknickknacks!

08:23.536 --> 08:25.303
The whole biker thing,
I mean it's...

08:25.438 --> 08:26.905
It's just a blip.

08:27.040 --> 08:29.207
- Things have been a little
subpar lately.

08:29.342 --> 08:31.409
I've noticed a lot more
sand than usual

08:31.478 --> 08:34.079
In the lodge this morning.
- That's because I quit.

08:34.214 --> 08:36.881
I am a sand removal expert.

08:36.884 --> 08:38.850
- You didn't quit,
you were fired.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.852
Katie: Fired. Of course.

08:40.921 --> 08:43.221
And I bet you didn't even
give her, her severance pay.

08:43.356 --> 08:44.723
- (gasping)

08:45.993 --> 08:48.326
- (chuckles)
see? Criminals.

08:48.328 --> 08:50.729
And I won't rest until you,
your family,

08:50.731 --> 08:52.964
And that dump of a moonshine

08:53.033 --> 08:54.699
Are gone for good.

08:54.701 --> 08:56.601
(evil chuckle)

09:02.042 --> 09:06.277
♪♪♪

09:06.346 --> 09:08.045
(footsteps crunch
in the foliage)

09:08.081 --> 09:09.981
- Oh, hey, ani.

09:10.017 --> 09:11.916
- Since you seem to be the one
in charge around here,

09:11.919 --> 09:13.985
What the hell is going on?
Sammy won't talk.

09:16.423 --> 09:17.722
- Uh...

09:17.758 --> 09:21.459
In the spirit of honesty
and family,

09:21.528 --> 09:22.928
(blows out breath)

09:24.565 --> 09:26.931
It started with a smidge
of drug smuggling,

09:26.934 --> 09:29.200
Which led to...

09:30.270 --> 09:32.437
Some light money laundering,

09:32.506 --> 09:34.339
And that resulted in...
Just a hint of hijacking.

09:34.341 --> 09:35.873
- You're joking, right?

09:36.009 --> 09:38.043
- We were having financial
trouble.

09:38.045 --> 09:39.744
Are... Having financial trouble.

09:39.879 --> 09:42.213
So, I agreed to get into
business with a man

09:42.215 --> 09:44.282
Who's a real criminal,

09:44.284 --> 09:45.984
And now, he's blackmailing me.

09:46.053 --> 09:48.019
Us, the family, and oh,

09:48.021 --> 09:50.021
This sounds so much worse
when I say it out loud.

09:50.023 --> 09:52.490
- Could sammy be implicated
in any of this?

09:52.559 --> 09:54.626
- No. No.
- Okay.

09:54.761 --> 09:56.994
- Maybe just in the smuggling
of chinese pharmaceuticals

09:57.030 --> 09:59.965
And money laundering,
but not to worry, I'm on it.

10:00.100 --> 10:03.267
By labour day, this will all
be yet another...

10:03.303 --> 10:05.837
Fun summer tale in
the finley-cullen canon.

10:05.906 --> 10:08.039
- And I thought I was
the headline this week.

10:08.108 --> 10:10.842
- Look, ani, I know how...

10:10.911 --> 10:13.444
Unusual our family

10:13.480 --> 10:15.546
Situation may look.

10:17.451 --> 10:18.683
But I'm gonna sort this out.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.720
- I hope you do.

10:21.722 --> 10:23.788
But I won't be around
to see it.

10:23.923 --> 10:25.724
My flight is tomorrow.

10:25.859 --> 10:28.459
And I'm gonna ask sammy
to come with me.

10:30.930 --> 10:32.664
- Oh.

10:34.401 --> 10:36.267
(waves lap in the distance)

10:36.269 --> 10:37.802
(footsteps crunch)

10:37.804 --> 10:43.441
♪♪♪

10:43.443 --> 10:45.242
(engine rumbles)

10:46.279 --> 10:47.845
(cuts engine)

10:48.949 --> 10:51.449
(door opens, shuts)

10:52.786 --> 10:54.385
- Got some big news.

10:54.454 --> 10:55.820
- You bought another house
without telling me?

10:55.822 --> 10:58.089
- Fine. I jumped the gun.

10:59.192 --> 11:01.226
I'm sorry.

11:01.361 --> 11:03.294
I just thought women
liked a grand gesture.

11:03.363 --> 11:05.496
- According to who?
Sensitive man weekly?

11:05.532 --> 11:06.997
- Yeah, maybe.

11:08.468 --> 11:10.034
But you know what else
sensitive man weekly says?

11:10.037 --> 11:11.536
- No.

11:11.671 --> 11:14.105
- If you love someone,
hurtful sarcasm is not a thing.

11:15.342 --> 11:17.641
- It's just a lot, ter.
- Yeah, I know.

11:20.213 --> 11:24.049
Which is why,
from this moment forward,

11:25.452 --> 11:27.017
I am here only to support you.

11:29.289 --> 11:30.821
I'm taking a leave
of absence from work.

11:32.659 --> 11:34.825
So I can come with you to la.

11:34.861 --> 11:36.761
Well, this new job
is a big deal for you,

11:36.896 --> 11:39.931
And this relationship
is a big deal for me.

11:40.000 --> 11:43.033
What the hell, right?
It'll be an adventure.

11:44.137 --> 11:49.807
♪♪♪

11:49.843 --> 11:51.675
Rhian: Oscar!
- Hmm, yeah?

11:51.712 --> 11:53.278
- Effective immediately,
you are now also

11:53.413 --> 11:55.413
The head of pr for
the moonshine.

11:55.482 --> 11:58.082
- I've been kinda into my new
gig at foxton pd.

11:58.151 --> 12:00.018
- Thirty katie's trying
to shut us down.

12:00.020 --> 12:02.720
She has a petition, oscar.
A petition!

12:02.723 --> 12:05.423
And guess what her precious
petition is clipped to?

12:06.993 --> 12:09.160
- A clipboard?
- That's my thing, goddamn it!

12:09.295 --> 12:11.195
There's only room for one
clipboard in this town.

12:11.264 --> 12:13.431
We need to fight back.
- How, exactly?

12:13.566 --> 12:15.633
- Little oink.
Win him over

12:15.702 --> 12:17.869
And we secure public opinion
among the campers.

12:17.871 --> 12:20.672
That is your first order of
business as the head of pr.

12:20.674 --> 12:22.573
- You say that
as if I have staff.

12:22.609 --> 12:27.645
♪♪♪

12:29.449 --> 12:30.815
- Is this really necessary?

12:30.950 --> 12:32.784
- As official moonshine
representatives,

12:32.919 --> 12:36.221
It is our duty to look united
and respectable,

12:36.223 --> 12:38.856
In order to woo back
our number one seasonal.

12:38.892 --> 12:40.858
We have to convince little oink
that this family

12:40.894 --> 12:42.860
Is more than just a near
bankrupt campground

12:42.996 --> 12:44.996
Overrun with criminals
and fiends!

12:45.131 --> 12:47.031
- How?
- Pitch me.

12:47.167 --> 12:48.766
I'm all ears.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.468
- (annoyed sigh)

12:50.537 --> 12:53.004
(rock music plays)

12:53.139 --> 13:00.111
♪♪♪

13:00.113 --> 13:07.084
♪♪♪

13:07.120 --> 13:14.025
♪♪♪

13:14.160 --> 13:21.299
♪♪♪

13:21.301 --> 13:23.033
Little oink: Ugh!

13:24.271 --> 13:25.970
(grunting)

13:25.972 --> 13:27.972
Ow! My back!

13:28.107 --> 13:30.007
(door slams shut)

13:31.645 --> 13:33.143
(hand taps gently,
footsteps recede)

13:34.181 --> 13:36.914
♪♪♪

13:36.983 --> 13:39.317
- So, you decided to go?
- No. Maybe.

13:39.452 --> 13:41.186
Stop rushing me!

13:41.321 --> 13:42.920
You're worse than terry.

13:43.056 --> 13:45.923
- So, it's official.
The whole town hates us.

13:46.059 --> 13:47.725
Don't worry,
I have oscar on it.

13:47.861 --> 13:49.159
Did you reason with gale?

13:49.196 --> 13:50.962
- Tried. Failed.

13:51.031 --> 13:52.930
He seems to think
he and his club

13:52.966 --> 13:54.798
Can just take over
the moonshine,

13:54.835 --> 13:56.267
And what's even
more disturbing

13:56.269 --> 13:57.835
Is I'm still
so attracted to him.

13:57.838 --> 13:59.837
- Oh, my god!
I'm gonna lose everything.

13:59.840 --> 14:01.639
End up raising my kids
in the woods.

14:01.675 --> 14:03.674
Bathing in the ocean.
Eating squirrels.

14:05.345 --> 14:07.411
- Thank you for that
filthy, hillbilly segue.

14:07.447 --> 14:09.614
It just reminded me of what
may now be our only option.

14:10.817 --> 14:12.550
Jill leblanc.
- I told her it was a bad idea.

14:12.685 --> 14:14.052
- You knew about this?

14:14.187 --> 14:16.220
- Didn't think she was actually
gonna go through with it.

14:16.223 --> 14:17.922
Are you actually
going through with it?

14:17.991 --> 14:19.823
- This is not a war
we can win on our own,

14:19.860 --> 14:21.258
And the only thing scarier
than a marauder--

14:21.294 --> 14:23.160
- The birthing video I watched
online this morning?

14:23.230 --> 14:25.630
- A loving, supportive partner?
- A leblanc!

14:25.699 --> 14:27.398
Think about it.
Jill's stuck in prison.

14:27.467 --> 14:29.567
All her assets have been frozen
so she can't make bail.

14:29.569 --> 14:31.469
She needs just as much
as we need her.

14:31.538 --> 14:33.571
- We have no money!

14:33.706 --> 14:36.240
- She has my money
hidden somewhere.

14:36.309 --> 14:38.309
Foxton pd never found
my duffle bag of cash

14:38.311 --> 14:40.511
When they busted her.

14:40.513 --> 14:42.780
- The enemy of my enemy
is a friend of mine.

14:42.849 --> 14:44.649
Okay. I'm aligned.

14:44.784 --> 14:46.250
Let's do this.
I'll drive.

14:46.253 --> 14:48.218
- No, I need to talk
to jill on my own,

14:48.255 --> 14:50.521
One businesswoman,

14:50.557 --> 14:52.123
Slash failed matriarch,
to the other.

14:52.125 --> 14:53.925
And I need crystal
to get me in.

14:54.060 --> 14:56.193
- So, this is it, then?

14:56.263 --> 14:58.863
This is war!

14:58.865 --> 15:01.532
- Battle up, bitches!
- Ugh!

15:01.534 --> 15:03.100
(rock music)
come on, do the thing!

15:03.169 --> 15:04.835
- No, I'm not.
- Up high.

15:04.905 --> 15:06.271
- Nora.
- Oh, my god.

15:06.406 --> 15:08.306
- War!
- Yes!

15:11.945 --> 15:15.546
♪♪♪

15:15.548 --> 15:17.147
(brakes squeak)

15:17.183 --> 15:19.484
(cuts engine)

15:19.619 --> 15:21.052
(doors creak open, shut)

15:21.121 --> 15:22.787
<i> Lidia: Hi. (giggles)</i>

15:22.789 --> 15:25.356
Um, oh,

15:25.392 --> 15:27.191
Crystal leblanc.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.694
(card snaps)

15:29.829 --> 15:32.530
That's me!

15:32.532 --> 15:34.231
Thanks!

15:36.636 --> 15:38.769
(gate creaks shut)

15:38.805 --> 15:40.771
(lock clicks open)

15:43.310 --> 15:45.376
(door clunks shut)

15:45.412 --> 15:49.647
♪♪♪

15:49.782 --> 15:51.549
(hand taps on bench)

15:51.684 --> 15:57.054
♪♪♪

15:57.123 --> 15:58.856
(nervous chuckle)
(door creaks open)

15:58.925 --> 16:01.925
♪♪♪

16:01.962 --> 16:04.261
(lock buzzes,
metal door creaks open)

16:04.297 --> 16:11.202
♪♪♪

16:11.337 --> 16:14.438
♪♪♪

16:14.507 --> 16:16.040
Lidia: Hear me out.

16:16.175 --> 16:17.741
Two minutes, tops.

16:17.777 --> 16:19.177
- Why the hell should
I do that?

16:19.179 --> 16:20.945
- Because I wanna make a deal

16:20.947 --> 16:22.079
And in the grand
scheme of things,

16:22.215 --> 16:25.016
May benefit you more than me.

16:28.287 --> 16:30.555
- I assume this has something
to do with the marauders

16:30.690 --> 16:32.756
Setting up camp?
- You heard?

16:32.792 --> 16:34.559
- What'd you think,
he was in it for your...

16:34.694 --> 16:36.760
Pretty blue eyes?
- Maybe.

16:37.897 --> 16:40.364
- Gale favreau and his merry
gang of thugs

16:40.433 --> 16:43.234
Have always only
had one goal in mind,

16:43.369 --> 16:45.470
To find a primo spot in foxton

16:45.472 --> 16:47.605
To use for their
own operations.

16:47.607 --> 16:49.640
- To be fair, I used gale too.

16:49.642 --> 16:51.843
Over, and over, and over again.

16:51.978 --> 16:53.577
(deep inhale and exhale)

16:53.646 --> 16:55.379
- What do you want?

16:55.448 --> 16:57.782
- I want us to work together.

16:57.851 --> 17:00.584
The leblancs and finley-cullens
back in action,

17:00.620 --> 17:02.720
To make sure foxton isn't
overrun by criminals

17:02.789 --> 17:04.388
Who aren't us.

17:04.391 --> 17:06.724
- Pass.
- Jill.

17:06.859 --> 17:08.960
You're being held for trial

17:08.962 --> 17:10.461
Because you can't raise
money for bail.

17:10.596 --> 17:12.396
And you can't get bail

17:12.465 --> 17:15.132
Because the rcmp froze
your dirty accounts.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.301
- I'm done here.
- I know you have my money.

17:17.437 --> 17:20.337
The duffle bag of cash,
$150k,

17:20.407 --> 17:22.306
Which whew,

17:22.308 --> 17:24.408
Would bring up
a lot of questions

17:24.411 --> 17:26.143
If your unemployed,

17:26.179 --> 17:28.179
Criminal relative
showed up with it.

17:28.314 --> 17:30.514
But tell me where it is,

17:30.550 --> 17:33.283
And I'll post bail tonight.

17:33.285 --> 17:34.218
♪♪♪

17:40.660 --> 17:42.693
- But to be clear,

17:42.762 --> 17:44.962
I'm doing this because
foxton is my turf.

17:44.998 --> 17:47.432
You get me outta here
and bring me gale,

17:47.567 --> 17:49.767
And my guys will move in

17:49.902 --> 17:51.903
And beat the crap outta
the marauders.

17:52.038 --> 17:54.505
I'll take care of the rest.

17:56.910 --> 17:58.509
And by the way,
you can tell my daughter

17:58.545 --> 18:00.778
To get the hell outta my house.

18:00.847 --> 18:03.514
I don't appreciate her
sending you in her place.

18:04.551 --> 18:06.650
Though, I have to admit,

18:06.686 --> 18:09.720
You do look great in hot pink.

18:10.790 --> 18:12.623
Now, about that money.

18:15.929 --> 18:17.462
(lid rattles)

18:17.597 --> 18:19.797
Lidia: Gotta hand it to jill
for her money hiding ingenuity.

18:21.000 --> 18:22.600
- What is with this summer
and assembly lines

18:22.602 --> 18:24.201
Of illegal behaviour?

18:24.237 --> 18:26.003
Life was so much easier
back in may

18:26.072 --> 18:27.271
When I was having
an illicit love affair

18:27.406 --> 18:29.206
With my sister's husband,

18:29.242 --> 18:31.809
And was content knowing I would
die in shame and obscurity.

18:31.944 --> 18:33.510
- Oh, poor, poor nora,

18:33.546 --> 18:35.480
On the verge of celebrity,
and in love with a man

18:35.615 --> 18:37.615
Who doesn't put his needs
before hers.

18:37.617 --> 18:39.150
Can't you see this
is a beautiful thing?

18:39.285 --> 18:41.018
- Know what's beautiful?

18:41.154 --> 18:42.419
The fact that you are using
your hard-earned money

18:42.489 --> 18:44.188
To bail out the woman
you put in jail.

18:44.257 --> 18:46.557
Here's a thought.
Why don't we leave her to rot,

18:46.593 --> 18:49.092
And you know,
pay off our tax debt?

18:49.129 --> 18:52.029
- No. Jill's the only way
of saving the moonshine.

18:52.165 --> 18:53.630
We bail her out,
hand over gale,

18:53.666 --> 18:55.366
Let the criminal cards
fall where they may.

18:55.368 --> 18:56.967
Questions?

18:57.003 --> 18:58.969
<i> Crystal: Yeah, um, ooh.</i>

18:59.005 --> 19:01.104
Uh, can you guys lock up
when you're done?

19:01.141 --> 19:03.040
The key's under
the legless gnome.

19:03.076 --> 19:05.375
- You got it.
You okay?

19:05.411 --> 19:07.178
You sure you have
a place to go?

19:07.313 --> 19:10.080
You wanna come home with me?
- Oh no! I'm fine.

19:10.116 --> 19:11.782
Next stop, destiny!

19:11.818 --> 19:13.517
Right? (nervous giggle)

19:13.520 --> 19:15.386
- Okay. Come here.

19:15.455 --> 19:20.324
♪♪♪

19:20.326 --> 19:22.259
<i> (bag rattles)</i>

19:24.130 --> 19:25.930
(lawn chair clatters)

19:25.932 --> 19:27.331
(tires rumble)

19:27.466 --> 19:29.500
(brakes squeak)

19:29.635 --> 19:33.437
♪♪♪

19:33.573 --> 19:35.873
Little oink: Oh shit!
- Hey.

19:35.942 --> 19:38.009
You need a hand, friend?

19:38.144 --> 19:40.544
Maybe that lawn chair is trying
to tell you something.

19:40.613 --> 19:42.346
- Reading tea leaves

19:42.481 --> 19:44.348
In a lazy lounge
recliner deluxe?

19:44.350 --> 19:46.617
Not gonna convince me to stay.

19:46.752 --> 19:49.553
- Well, that's too bad.

19:49.556 --> 19:52.957
This rum...
Might be my best ever.

19:53.026 --> 19:54.758
Come on.

19:54.794 --> 19:56.560
Stay for my party.

19:56.563 --> 19:58.362
Could be our last.

19:58.398 --> 20:00.364
- Look, rum,

20:00.400 --> 20:02.433
No, it's just not
gonna fix this.

20:02.435 --> 20:04.769
- History begs to differ.

20:04.904 --> 20:07.571
Do you know that rum
is the cornerstone beverage

20:07.640 --> 20:09.974
Of the west indies,
the maritime provinces,

20:09.976 --> 20:11.875
Newfoundland and labrador?

20:11.911 --> 20:13.277
It's a drink of community.

20:13.412 --> 20:16.447
A way for friends
to come together.

20:16.516 --> 20:19.083
Especially in times of trouble.
- (scoffs)

20:19.218 --> 20:21.919
I want to stay your friend,
ken, I really do,

20:22.054 --> 20:23.921
But your allies are bailing.

20:23.990 --> 20:25.790
And looks like you are, too.

20:25.925 --> 20:28.059
Your daughters appear
to be the only ones

20:28.194 --> 20:30.861
Willing to fight for this
place.

20:30.996 --> 20:32.930
For shame, good sir.

20:32.932 --> 20:34.798
For shame.

20:34.834 --> 20:41.338
♪♪♪

20:42.375 --> 20:45.309
(footsteps crunch
in the foliage)

20:45.378 --> 20:49.080
♪♪♪

20:49.215 --> 20:51.014
- I hear you're...

20:51.050 --> 20:52.616
Taking over our business.

20:53.953 --> 20:55.286
- Huh.

20:55.421 --> 20:57.688
- I hope we can find
some common ground.

20:58.958 --> 21:01.125
- Well, that's big of you.

21:01.127 --> 21:02.659
- I suppose it is.

21:03.763 --> 21:05.830
Want a drink?

21:05.965 --> 21:08.633
- Uh, what the hell.

21:10.503 --> 21:12.069
(alcohol burbles)

21:14.941 --> 21:16.507
(thumb taps on phone)

21:16.509 --> 21:18.142
<i> Rhian: You shopping for la</i>

21:18.277 --> 21:20.044
Or every member of the
broken social scene, ever?

21:20.113 --> 21:22.146
- You obliterate
weeds to chill.

21:22.148 --> 21:23.981
I window shop.

21:24.116 --> 21:26.250
(door creaks open)
(lidia sighs)

21:26.252 --> 21:27.652
- Okay.

21:27.787 --> 21:29.654
Bail's been posted.

21:29.789 --> 21:31.455
Jill's getting released
tomorrow.

21:31.457 --> 21:33.858
Only thing left to do
is deliver gale to jill.

21:33.993 --> 21:36.293
- And I have a plan.
- Hmm.

21:36.296 --> 21:37.928
(paper crinkling)

21:39.332 --> 21:40.998
It involves--
- no, no violence, rhian.

21:41.133 --> 21:42.532
- (grumbles)

21:43.736 --> 21:46.337
Then we go to plan b.
Use your magic pumpum.

21:46.472 --> 21:48.405
- Magic pumpum?

21:48.407 --> 21:49.873
- Oscar and I have
been researching

21:49.909 --> 21:51.675
How to explain body parts
to the unborn twins,

21:51.678 --> 21:54.244
And the word for vagina that
resonated most for me,

21:54.280 --> 21:55.746
Was "pumpum".

21:55.815 --> 21:57.414
- There's no way I'm having
sex with gale

21:57.450 --> 21:59.082
Now that he's a confirmed
murderer.

21:59.118 --> 22:01.118
- Oh, look who suddenly
has standards.

22:01.187 --> 22:02.453
- (gasps)
- whoa!

22:02.522 --> 22:04.488
- God, where did you get that?
- Dark web.

22:04.490 --> 22:06.890
- Can't you online shop
like a normal person?

22:06.926 --> 22:09.160
Lidia: Seriously.
- At least I checkout,

22:09.162 --> 22:11.428
And not just of my life
and relationships.

22:11.464 --> 22:13.197
- Okay.

22:13.332 --> 22:14.898
(paper crinkles)
- back to plan a.

22:14.934 --> 22:16.567
(loud thud then grunt outside)

22:16.636 --> 22:19.103
♪♪♪

22:19.105 --> 22:20.838
(door creaks open)
- (gasps)

22:20.973 --> 22:22.672
- You lose somethin'?

22:24.177 --> 22:25.642
- Oh, my god.

22:25.678 --> 22:28.212
- He's a big fan of my rum.
- Huh.

22:28.214 --> 22:29.980
He knew big, bad,
biker boy's a lightweight?

22:30.049 --> 22:32.116
- My moonshine is lethal.

22:32.118 --> 22:35.186
And I clocked the son
of a bitch.

22:36.289 --> 22:38.856
- Yes!

22:38.991 --> 22:40.724
- This works too!

22:44.597 --> 22:46.530
(waves lap)

22:46.532 --> 22:52.937
♪♪♪

22:53.072 --> 22:55.005
- Hey. I uh,

22:55.074 --> 22:57.174
I wanted to give you this.

22:57.243 --> 22:59.009
It's a marijuana plant.

22:59.011 --> 23:00.510
Represents growth.

23:01.747 --> 23:04.315
Hopefully my own.
Soon to be this plant's.

23:04.450 --> 23:06.483
(playful laugher
in the distance)

23:10.222 --> 23:12.155
- My first van warming gift.

23:12.191 --> 23:14.158
- Hmm?

23:14.227 --> 23:16.693
- Oh uh, this my new home.

23:16.695 --> 23:19.897
Uh, my mom kicked me out,
so now I am...

23:19.899 --> 23:22.299
Child of the tides.

23:22.301 --> 23:25.101
You know, owned by no one
but the sea.

23:25.138 --> 23:27.171
- You know, you could move back
into the trailer with--

23:27.306 --> 23:28.906
- No.

23:28.908 --> 23:31.274
You need to concentrate on you.

23:31.310 --> 23:33.276
You have stopped drinking.

23:33.312 --> 23:36.046
And fate has brought your first
love back to you,

23:36.082 --> 23:37.915
And you have a...
- No.

23:37.984 --> 23:39.516
- A brother-son to think about.

23:39.585 --> 23:41.719
- I really don't need to
concentrate, crystal because--

23:41.721 --> 23:43.420
- I do.

23:43.423 --> 23:45.188
You know, on my business,

23:45.224 --> 23:48.192
And on myself.

23:48.261 --> 23:49.860
And if the universe

23:49.896 --> 23:53.063
Decides to send something
beautiful my way

23:53.065 --> 23:54.798
I am ready,

23:54.801 --> 23:57.401
But if not, which is more
likely, then that's okay

23:57.470 --> 23:59.069
Because I am very accustomed

23:59.138 --> 24:00.838
To being let down.
- Crystal--

24:00.840 --> 24:03.740
- And by the way,
a marijuana plant

24:03.776 --> 24:05.609
Does not signify growth.

24:07.947 --> 24:09.980
So, if you will excuse me,

24:10.115 --> 24:12.416
You are blocking my view.

24:12.418 --> 24:19.356
♪♪♪

24:19.425 --> 24:24.795
♪♪♪

24:24.797 --> 24:27.431
♪ oh, oh

24:27.500 --> 24:29.834
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh

24:29.969 --> 24:33.170
♪♪♪

24:33.172 --> 24:35.639
(waves lap)

24:35.641 --> 24:38.509
♪♪♪

24:38.511 --> 24:40.311
(slippers clap lightly)

24:40.313 --> 24:44.614
♪♪♪

24:49.989 --> 24:51.889
- Hear you're heading
out tomorrow.

24:52.024 --> 24:53.857
- Uh, yeah.

24:56.229 --> 24:57.728
(footstep thud)

25:01.868 --> 25:04.401
(sighs) I don't know
how you did it.

25:04.470 --> 25:05.869
All these kids.

25:07.673 --> 25:10.407
- Emotional whack-a-mole.

25:10.476 --> 25:13.276
With the occasional
bout of joy.

25:16.883 --> 25:18.615
- Thank you for raising him.

25:18.684 --> 25:21.018
He's incredible.

25:21.020 --> 25:24.154
And I know a big part
of that is because of you.

25:24.290 --> 25:26.023
- All we can do is try.

25:26.092 --> 25:27.591
- (teary exhale)

25:30.196 --> 25:32.195
I did try, you know.

25:32.231 --> 25:34.264
I loved that little
baby so much.

25:36.869 --> 25:38.702
For the first time in my life
I had someone

25:38.704 --> 25:40.670
Who loved me unconditionally.

25:43.109 --> 25:45.242
But it was selfish.

25:45.244 --> 25:48.311
I was a kid,
and he deserved more.

25:48.347 --> 25:49.847
- For the record...

25:53.052 --> 25:55.218
It's you who deserves thanks.

25:55.254 --> 25:57.687
Sammy changed my life.

26:00.126 --> 26:02.326
All of our lives,
for the better.

26:04.130 --> 26:07.431
Whatever happens, just know
you have lots of people

26:07.433 --> 26:09.633
Who love you unconditionally
now.

26:09.768 --> 26:16.740
♪♪♪

26:16.742 --> 26:22.379
♪♪♪

26:22.381 --> 26:23.880
- (lidia grunts) jesus!
- Oh, god!

26:23.916 --> 26:26.416
Is that muscle or leather?
- To the chair, to the chair.

26:26.452 --> 26:28.085
- To the chair? Okay.
- Yeah, back him in.

26:28.087 --> 26:30.086
- Okay.
Nora: This is hard.

26:30.122 --> 26:32.790
- Okay, give a nice bump.
- Okay! Yep! Ugh!

26:32.792 --> 26:34.891
- Slide back.
- Oh yeah.

26:34.927 --> 26:37.060
- Okay. Oh, look.
- Okay, yeah.

26:37.096 --> 26:39.430
- Let's throw some
sunnies on him.

26:39.432 --> 26:41.765
Grab some duct tape,
and we're good to go.

26:41.834 --> 26:44.101
No one will be the wiser.

26:44.103 --> 26:45.569
- Yeah, we take turns
guarding him

26:45.638 --> 26:47.104
Until jill's guys show up.
- And then,

26:47.173 --> 26:49.239
Jill and gale will have
a reasonable conversation,

26:49.241 --> 26:51.241
Where they'll come up with a
mutually beneficial compromise.

26:51.377 --> 26:53.043
Ha.

26:53.079 --> 26:55.378
- Lidia, you want
the cobra dead,

26:55.414 --> 26:57.181
You bite the head off
the cobra!

26:57.316 --> 26:59.049
(ominous music)

27:00.119 --> 27:02.585
- Oh, god!
Oh, god, you're right.

27:04.190 --> 27:06.256
Jill's gonna kill gale.

27:06.325 --> 27:13.163
♪♪♪

27:13.165 --> 27:15.098
(realizing exhales)

27:15.134 --> 27:16.934
Is this who we are now?

27:17.069 --> 27:19.335
As messed up as our enemies?
- Ugh.

27:19.372 --> 27:21.405
- With no moral compass?

27:21.540 --> 27:24.008
Willing to do anything
to protect

27:24.143 --> 27:26.143
A soggy patch of dirt,
and pile of old wood?

27:27.480 --> 27:28.946
Oh, god.

